President Uhuru Kenyatta&rsquo;s Jubilee Party has affirmed it will abide by the court ruling appealed by the IEBC challenging the announcement of the presidential tally at the constituency as final.JP secretary general Raphael Tuju termed the opposition&rsquo;s threat of boycotting the August 8 polls a &ldquo;grave disregard for the rule of law and a direct threat to public security&rdquo;. NASA leaders said they will not participate in the general election if the Court of Appeal fails to dismiss IEBC&rsquo;s appeal.NASA&rsquo;s flagbearer Raila Odinga and his Pentagon brigades have maintained the IEBC chaired by Wafula Chebukati should abide by last month&rsquo;s High Court ruling stopping any changes to presidential results announced at the constituency level when transmitted to national tallying centre.